# Root .vercelignore — safety net for the vgp-web project.
#
# The working tree carries private material that must never reach a deploy:
# executed legal evidence, signatures, handoff bundles, audio masters.
# Vercel does NOT read .gitignore, so untracked private files WOULD be
# uploaded without this file.
#
# ⚠️ ANCHOR DIRECTORY PATTERNS WITH A LEADING SLASH.
# These patterns use .gitignore semantics: `flowstate/` (no leading slash)
# matches a directory named "flowstate" at ANY depth. That silently deleted
# `app/api/founder/flowstate/route.ts` from the bundle and made the founder
# dashboard's Flowstate panel return 404. Use `/flowstate/` to mean
# "the flowstate directory at the repo root, and nothing else".

# Legal evidence, executed contracts, intake material
/legal-intake/
**/output/legal-private/
**/signatures/
**/*signature*

# Handoff bundles and prompt archives (root level only)
/*.zip
/*HANDOFF*
/*ANTIGRAVITY*

# The Flow app is a separate Vercel project (flowstate) with its own root
# directory, and is already excluded from the root tsconfig. Anchored so it
# cannot match app/api/founder/flowstate/ or any other nested path.
/flowstate/

# Scratch and working notes (root level only)
/scratch/
/.playwright-cli/

# Build output and caches — these legitimately appear nested, so they stay
# unanchored on purpose.
node_modules/
.next/
**/.wrangler/
*.local
